added.title: Teen Titans Action
added.description: The Titans learn that toys from comedy shows don't sell, so they become action heroes and are awarded a toy license deal with the Toy Master. But, when they grow tired of the action lifestyle the Titans go on a mission to destroy Toy Master's heavily armed cosmic toy factory to get out of their contract.

added.title: TV Knight 8
added.description: Teen Titans Go takes a comedic look at the superheroes' lives. Viewers finally get the opportunity to watch what life is like for the super teens when their capes are left at home. The teens will deal with everyday issues of adolescence including laundry contests and quests to construct the perfect sandwich.

added.title: Hashtag #1 Fan
added.description: Panda gets kidnapped by a pair of deranged French foxes.

added.title: Snow Place Like Home
added.description: When the Bears realize whatever they build with snow comes to life they decide to build the biggest snow party of all time.

added.title: Fiesta Day
added.description: The Bears party it up with a living piñatas for Fiesta Day. Wanting the festivities to never end, Grizz wishes for it to be Fiesta Day everyday.

added.title: Baba Yaga House
added.description: Squatter Otter tries to win Panda's trust and convince the Bears to live in a mysterious house.

added.title: Bears in the Dark
added.description: The Bears search for their missing box in a dark and scary cave.

added.title: Duck Duck Juice
added.description: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

added.title: Cluckwork Orange
added.description: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bad bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.

added.title: Free Chili
added.description: When Owen hides a walkie-talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

added.title: The Date
added.description: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, this gives Owen & Jude the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

added.title: Aquarium for a Dream
added.description: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

added.title: Bridge Out
added.description: After an overpass collapses on the highway, Team Tennyson is in a traffic jam along with Simon Sez and family. But when Ben and Simon team up to tackle the gridlock together, Simon only makes matters much, much worse.

added.title: Beach Heads
added.description: After traveling to Tampa Beach, Florida, Team Tennyson hopes to get some much-needed rest & relaxation, but the tempests without a temper, the Weatherheads, have other plans that Ben must thwart: to build a new beach base!

added.title: Charm School's Out
added.description: During a family cookout at a forest campsite, Charmcaster users her magic to switch places with Gwen, but when Ben catches "Charmcaster" sneaking about, he attacks, unaware it's actually his cursed cousin!

added.title: Billy Bajillions
added.description: In Aspen, Colorado, Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max are on a hike to find the Forgeti, but when they realize they've stumbled upon Billy Billions own "Winter in July" ski resort, Ben must battle Billy, with an assist from the Forgeti itself.

added.title: Franken-Fight
added.description: Ben hops into the Rustbuggy for a driving lesson along the sand dunes of Cape Cod, but he takes a freaky switchback turn when the Rustbuggy is mutated into a motor-monster by Bootleg, another alien transformation of Kevin 11, with powers similar to Upgrade!

added.title: T.G.I.S
added.description: The Secret Saturdays come to Bellwood to investigate a rash of chupacabra attacks.

added.title: Food Around the Corner
added.description: Ben as Gravattack attempts to moderate a fragile peace treaty, but must endure the attacks of tiny alien fleas, which have inhabited his body.

added.title: O Mother, Where Art Thou?
added.description: Ma Vreedle threatens to blow up the sun if Ben and the Plumbers don't find her missing son!

added.title: Return to Forever
added.description: The Forever Knights threaten to use a sinister weapon to erase all alien DNA on Earth unless Ben and Rook can stop them.

added.title: Mud Is Thicker Than Water
added.description: Ben, Gwen and Cousin Lucy try to find out how Psyphon's thugs are getting Plumber technology.

added.title: Grief Bringer
added.description: Nya and Kai, who have become the respective leaders of the Munce and Geckles, attempt to unite the tribes in an effort to defeat their mutual enemy, the Skull Sorcerer, who schemes against them.

added.title: Masters Never Quit
added.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

added.title: The Darkest Hour
added.description: Forced to flee by the arrival of Grief-Bringer, the ninja, the Munce and the Geckles take refuge in the Geckle Strong-Cave. But the bitter feud between Munce and Geckles threatens to tear them apart, just when unity is needed most…when they are about to confront the Skull Sorcerer and Grief-Bringer!

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: The Upply Strike Back!
added.description: Cole and the Upply arrive at the Skull Sorcerer's keep in the hopes of rescuing Lloyd and the other ninja. But in order to do so, Cole will need to retrieve his mother's fabled swords, the Blades of Deliverance, which are hidden somewhere inside the keep!

added.title: Magnus P.I.
added.description: There's a been a string of thefts and each one has involved a Bakugan. The AAAnimus security force have decided the only brawler who could be responsible is: Magnus. The shock of this accusation sets Magnus off to takes justice in his own hands and go after the thief himself./Magnus foils the latest burglary attempt by the phantom thief, and in doing so, discovers the brawler partners with a golden Bakugan.  Magnus is now more interested in a brawl, than stopping any crime.

added.title: Awesome Brawlers Training  Camp
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers head to a training facility owned by Kasami International to prepare for the Bakugan Battle League - Los Volmos. But once the gang figures out they will all be competing against each other for the same title, the "team building" retreat doesn't quite go as planned./Agit turns up at the Kasami training facility and fits right in with the Awesome brawlers. This is a lifestyle that he can get used to, but it becomes apparent Agit is torn between a life as a phantom thief and life as a brawler.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Begins/Riot vs. Ajit
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Begins: The qualifying rounds for the Bakugan Battle league are taking place all around Los Volmos. The Awesome Brawlers all make it through into the tournament without a hitch, that is all but Dan. Dan faces an old rival in Trey, who's back with a few tricks up his sleeve./Riot vs. Ajit: The Bakugan battle league is finally here and 16 brawlers have qualified to enter including all the Awesome Brawlers. The first round will feature a brawl between China Riot and the golden Bakugan brawler, Agit!

added.title: Kung Fu Master/A Battle of Popularity
added.description: Kung Fu Master: Dan's first match-up of the Bakugan battle league is the Chinese Champion Brawler: Zhao. His opponent is a deeply focused, and serious brawler, who uses Kung Fu techniques in battle. It's going to take all Dan and Drago's focus and strength to get through this opponent!/A Battle of Popularity: Shun and Wynton's first match-ups in the Bakugan battle league take place at the same time. Even though they're not battling each other, Wynton can't help getting a little competitive with Shun, bragging that he can get the crowd cheering louder than Shun. The brawls quickly turn into a popularity contest, instead of a Bakugan battle!

added.title: The Mysterious Revenger/Wynton vs. Lia
added.description: The Mysterious Revenger: It's the quarter finals of the Bakugan Battle League, the top eight brawlers are set to face off! In this round, Dan will face off against the Bakugan rocker - Revenger! These two brawlers give it their all in this icy cold clash!/Wynton Vs. Lia: The quarter finals continue, and it's the first Awesome Brawler vs. Awesome Brawler matches of the Bakugan Battle League tournament. In this round, it's Wynton vs. Lia and Shun vs. Lightning.

added.title: Luthor in Paradise
added.description: With the aid of Circe the Witch, Luthor travels to Paradise Island to steal an artifact that will give him god-like powers. When Superman and Batman arrive on the island to bring him back, they find that they're almost as popular with the Amazons as Luthor on this woman-only island.

added.title: Plastic Man Saves the World
added.description: Plastic Man feels shuffled off to the side as the Justice League battles Brainiac so he takes it upon himself to infiltrate the alien's ship on his own and thwart the villain's plans.

added.title: Field Trip
added.description: A group of teenage superheroes are being shown around the Fortress of Solitude when they inadvertently cause the phantom zone projector to trap Superman and release three Kryptonian criminals.

added.title: Rage of the Red Lanterns
added.description: Chased by the Red Lanterns, Lobo seeks sanctuary with the Justice League. As the League attempts to stave off the Red Lanterns, Lobo reveals the real reason he wants shelter in the Watchtower, he wants access to a powerful space weapon being held by our heroes.

added.title: Freezer Burn
added.description: Batman and Firestorm team up to fight their respective cold villains, Mr. Freeze and Killer Frost. Complications arise when Firestorm's infatuation for the wily Ms. Frost gets the best of him.

added.title: Cabeza de Playa
added.description: Después de viajar a Tampa Beach, Florida, el equipo Tennyson espera poder descansar y relajarse, pero las tempestades sin temperamento, los Climáticos, tienen otros planes que Ben debe frustrar: iconstruir una nueva base en la playa!

added.title: Encantadas
added.description: Durante una comida familiar en un campamento forestal, Charmcaster usa su magia para cambiar de lugar con Gwen, pero cuando Ben descubre a "Charmcaster" husmeando, ataca, sin darse cuenta de que en realidad es su hechizada prima.

added.title: Billy Billones
added.description: En Aspen, Colorado, Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max van de excursión para encontrar al Olvideti. Pero cuando se encuentran con la pista artificial de esquí de Billy Billones, Ben debe luchar contra Billy con la ayuda del propio Olvideti.

added.title: Molestando a los Bichos
added.description: El equipo de Tennyson viaja al Instituto Crisalín en busca de yoga a altas temperaturas y buenas vibraciones, solo para descubrir que los hermanos Bicho también están de vacaciones. Pero ¿los astutos insectoides están realmente de vacaciones, o están tramando otro de sus tontos planes?

added.title: Franken Pelea
added.description: Ben se sube al Rustbuggy para recibir una lección de conducción a lo largo de las dunas de Cabo Cod. Pero el plan da un extraño giro cuando el Rustbuggy se transforma en un monstruo motorizado por Bootleg, otra transformación alienígena de Kevin 11.

added.title: El Dragon Grief-Bringer
added.description: Nya y Kai, quienes se han convertido en los líderes de los Munces y Geckles, intentan unirlos para derrotar a su enemigo mutuo, el Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Los Maestros Nunca se Rinden
added.description: Cole, la princesa Vania, Wu y los humildes llegan a un templo, que una vez fue un campo de entrenamiento para los Maestros Elementales de la Tierra.

added.title: La Hora Mas Oscura
added.description: Los Ninjas, los Munces y los Geckles se refugian en la Cueva Fuerte Geckle , pero enfrentan al Hechicero Calavera y al Dragón Grief-Bringer.

added.title: El Ascenso
added.description: Cole, los de abajo, la princesa Vania y Wu salen de la montaña para enfrentarse al malvado Hechicero Calavera.

added.title: Los de Arriba Contra Atacan
added.description: Cole y los de abajo llegan para rescatar a los Ninjas. Para ello, Cole tendrá que recuperar las espadas legendarias, las Espadas de la Liberación.

added.title: Jugo arcoiris
added.description: Después de desafiarse unos a otros a tomar el Latte de Pegaso de Chef, Izzy y Jude están llenos de energía y Duncan y Courtney hacen un viaje por carretera para tratar de reemplazar la bebida antes de que Chef descubra que desapareció.

added.title: El pollo maniaco
added.description: Después de hacerse amigo de un pollo con mala actitud en un zoológico de contacto, este lo sigue de regreso a la escuela. Él defiende la mala conducta del ave hasta que ya no puede seguir haciéndolo.

added.title: Chile libre
added.description: Cuando Owen oculta un walkie talky dentro de su perro con chile, Harold cree que es un alienígena que vino a destruir la tierra.

added.title: La cita
added.description: Cuando Chef está feliz ordena pizza para los niños. Esto le da a Owen & Jude la idea de crear una falsa admiradora secreta para Chef.

added.title: La pecera de los suenos
added.description: Gwen trata de convencer a Chef de que le diga a la clase la verdad sobre su pececito dorado.

added.title: Stop That Ducky!
added.description: After snagging an ultra-fuel-cell upgrade, Penguin's Ducky Boat suddenly becomes the fastest vehicle in Gotham. Confident leader Bam must rally the Batwheels to stop the turbo-Ducky!

added.title: Buff's BFF
added.description: When Buff befriends Mr. Freeze's snowcrawler Snowy, the other Batwheels bristle at the thought of hanging out with a "bad guy…" so Buff sets out to change their minds.

added.title: Splash Zone
added.description: Mayor Foghorn Leghorn hires The Looney Builders to build a giant water slide for Looneyburg's waterpark. He keeps adding onto the design with the support of Bugs until problems arise.

added.title: Ice Creamed
added.description: It's Taz's birthday, so The Looney Builders build him a huge ice cream sundae. Porky worries about making a mistake and delays the build causing the ice cream to start to melt.

added.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
added.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

added.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
added.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

added.title: A Very Percy Valentine's Day
added.description: It's Valentine's Day and no one on Sodor is happier than Percy -- he gets to deliver everyone's gifts to their friends throughout the island! Unfortunately, his energetic eagerness turns to panic when an accident on the rails causes everyone's presents to fall in the mud! With Thomas' help, Percy discovers a way to still deliver the feelings behind everyone's presents -- by using the gift of song!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Valentine's Hearts
added.description: As the other engines prepare for a Valentine's Day party, Kana is worried: she doesn't know what to bring! Inspired by Sandy's giant metal heart surprise, Kana decides that she is going to create a sparkly big heart using her electricity! Through a series of accidents, Kana realizes that the best surprise she could bring to the party is herself!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Dragon Run
added.description: Thomas has the honor of pulling the dragon to the Medieval Faire, but everyone wants a turn as well.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Biggest Adventure Club
added.description: When Thomas finds a treasure map he creates "The Big Adventure Club," to seek the treasure, but when Sandy wants to join, Thomas says she's too little, so Sandy forms her own club.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Percy's Lucky Bell
added.description: When Thomas borrows Percy's lucky bell for a dangerous delivery, Thomas isn't careful and loses the bell.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: First Car
added.description: No kind of travel is too difficult for the BlippiMobile, not even TIME travel! Blippi and FETCH head back in time to see what the first cars were like, and who better to show him than Blippi's great-grandpa Blippi! It's a harrowing ride, but along the way Blippi finds the answers he's looking for.

added.title: Volcano
added.description: On a drive through the mountains, Blippi is nearly hit by a puff of smoke from a volcano vent! Curious about what makes a volcano erupt, Blippi and FETCH fly into the volcano. With some close calls, they watch Maggie the Magma Monster gobble up the floor and play a favorite game - The Floor is Lava!

added.title: Squirrels
added.description: Blippi and FETCH are going on a treasure hunt! For Squirrel treasure that is. Their new friend Sparky the Squirrel has her nuts buried all over the park and Blippi tries to remember where she buried them. Sparky remembers them all though and Blippi learns why squirrels bury their nuts.

added.title: Lellobee Lullaby
added.description: Come to sing the Lellobee Lullaby! It's nighttime at the farm. Mei and Ella are putting Carlos, Pablo, and Lettie to sleep in the barn. They tuck them in, give them milk and make sure they have their favorite in cuddly toys to snuggle.

added.title: The Team Work song
added.description: Join Ella, Rishi, Heidi, and Bingo in their teamwork making the farm more beautiful and tidy. Working as a team, they do some weeding, they paint the fence and they put some rubbish back into an overturned bin. Soon, the front of the farm is looking neat and they made it work together!

added.title: Wash Your Hands, Scrub That Soap
added.description: Ella is getting muddy. Mei comes out with a plate of dumplings, but Ella's hands are dirty!

added.title: Yes Yes Vegetables Song - Healthy Habits!
added.description: Baby Izzy doesn't like vegetables - until they sing a song with her!

added.title: No Monsters Scared of the Dark
added.description: The Baby Pumpkins are scared of the dark as they go to the halloween party!

added.title: Spin Out
added.description: Taz learns a tough lesson. He shouldn't spin after eating too much candy.

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: The babies experience their first snowfall.

added.title: Shadow of a Doubt
added.description: Tweety sheds some light on what a shadow is.

added.title: Christmas in July
added.description: The babies pretend it's Christmas in hopes of getting Lola the stethoscope she wants.

added.title: Bruce Bunny
added.description: When Daffy starts making up hurtful rhymes, Bugs changes his name to Bruce.
